212
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:12,170
an average family's drinking water for
about a month and a half.

213
00:15:13,420 --> 00:15:18,450
By May 2010, the program had reached over
4,000 participants and had

214
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:23,100
sold enough Gadyen Dlo to treat 12 million
liters of drinking water.

215
00:15:24,472 --> 00:15:28,910
In 2010, an impact evaluation was done in
northern Haiti

216
00:15:28,910 --> 00:15:31,800
and reported a few years later in a
scientific journal.

217
00:15:33,970 --> 00:15:37,590
The team found that 3/4ths of the randomly
selected households

218
00:15:37,590 --> 00:15:42,231
in the program area reported that they
were currently using Gadyen Dlo.

219
00:15:42,231 --> 00:15:47,880
And 56% of these households compared to
just 10% in controlled

220
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:53,750
areas had free chlorine residuals between
0.2 and 2 milligrams per liter.

221
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:56,540
Indicating that they were applying
chlorine correctly.

222
00:15:57,840 --> 00:16:00,810
This evaluation was made after the
earthquake in January

223
00:16:00,810 --> 00:16:04,560
2010, but focused on areas not affected by
the quake.

224
00:16:05,750 --> 00:16:09,930
The Gadyen Dlo program was extended to the
earthquake zone.

225
00:16:09,930 --> 00:16:15,130
And accelerated greatly after the onset of
cholera in the region in October 2010.

226
00:16:15,130 --> 00:16:19,170
Half a million bottles of Gadyen Dlo

227
00:16:19,170 --> 00:16:21,920
were distributed in the affected areas for
